args: *pant* *pant* I finally...made it down\nto the mountain path...
Wu Kong, is this not quite reckless?\nFor a novice sealer to try and control a\nrelic of the Su Jindan's standing...
Aw, it's fine! Even a newbie like me\noughta be able to keep it under control\nlong enough to reach old man Fa Ming.
*sigh* It seems there is no other option.\nClimb up on my back.
No can do. I'm holding the Su Jindan,\nremember? It'd be dangerous even for a\ndragon like you to get too close to me.
Just get up there alreadyâ€”for Xuan\nZang's sake, as well as your own.
Your thanks are not necessary.\nAnd now, we are away!
S-sorry... I'm losin' strength\nand can't really hold on...
Darn it! This stupid Su Jindan is\nmakin' me all kinds of drowsy.
You mustn't fall asleep; if you are\nconsumed by its power, you will be\ntrapped in its spell of false immortality.
Endure, Wu Kong. If you can get this relic\nback, there is no doubt that Fa Ming\nwill accept you as a sealer for true.
Do you not wish to get the better\nof the Qilin who denied you so?
Of course I do! And besides...
I just plain want to save him.
Oh? I thought you disliked him.
He's the one who don't like ME!\nFor me, it's more like...
Well, I just think he's really cool.\nHe's a great sealer, he's powerful,\nand I want to be like him.
But then he gets all, ï¼‚You're not a Qilin,\nyou'll never understand, blah blah blah,ï¼‚\nand there's nothing I can say.
History and race are great barriers\nto overcome for certain.

Greater still when we discuss the Qilin,
whose role in leading their civilization
to ruin due to their own depravity still
echoes forth today.
Yeah, but no matter how hard I work,\nI can never become one of them.
And no matter how hard I try to understand\ntheir experience, there's always going to\nbe some part of it that's a mystery.
But that's exactly what makes me want\nto reject the Qilin way of living.
They don't NEED to go so far in taking\nresponsibility for their pastâ€”there\nhas to be some other way.
So if I walk along outside the wall\nlong enough...then someday...
Someday there could be a future...\nwhere the Qilin don't condemn\nthemselves and...and they don't...
Open your eyes, boy!\nYou mustn't fall asleep!
I had no idea the Su Jindan's power was\nas dangerous as the Ling Xuan Dan's.
Your return was late, so I came\nback to check on your progress.
So this is the Su Jindan, is it?\nIf I could hold back its power,\neven for a short time...
...Whew! There. It shouldn't trouble\nus for a little while. Let us hurry back\nto my master and make him whole.
I will carry you on my back, Xuan Zang.
And I will hold onto Wu Kong.
